From: Christopher L. Crutchfield <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
Date: Sat, 26 Apr 2026 19:55:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ufs: exynos: drop UFSHCD_QUIRK_PRDT_BYTE_GRAN from gs201

The gs201 (Tensor G2 / Pixel Fold) entry in exynos_ufs_of_match was
added carrying the UFSHCD_QUIRK_PRDT_BYTE_GRAN quirk inherited from
gs101. On gs201 hardware this is wrong: the controller follows the
UFS spec strictly and interprets the UTRD's response_upiu_offset and
prd_table_offset fields in DWORDS, not bytes.

With the quirk set, ufshcd_host_memory_configure writes
response_upiu_offset = ALIGNED_UPIU_SIZE (i.e. 0x200, in bytes).
The controller reads 0x200 and interprets it as 0x200 dwords =
0x800 bytes, then writes its UPIU response at UCD+0x800. Mainline
reads the response slot at UCD+0x200 (per the C struct layout in
struct utp_transfer_cmd_desc) and sees nothing — exactly the
"controller signals UTRCS, doorbell clears, response slot stays
empty, no UIC errors" pattern that's been confounding gs201 UFS
bring-up.

Confirmed by stamping the response slot with 0xAB before submitting
NOP_OUT and dumping memory at the alternate location after the
controller "completes":

  RSP UPIU: 00000000: abababab abababab abababab abababab
  UCD+0x800 (alt rsp loc): 00000000: 00000020 00000000 00000000 00000000
                                     ^^^^^^^^
                                     NOP_IN (0x20) — the response

Dropping the quirk causes mainline to emit the offsets in DWORDS
(0x80 = 128 dwords = 0x200 bytes), which the controller now
correctly interprets, and NOP_OUT completes successfully. PWR_MODE
change to HS-G4 L2 succeeds afterwards (link comes up to FAST mode).

(Subsequent UFS init still hits a separate PHY CDR-lock issue, but
that's a distinct problem; this patch is the gating fix for getting
past NOP_OUT on gs201.)

The gs101 entry keeps the quirk untouched. gs101 hardware may have
the same DWORDS-per-spec behavior, in which case the quirk could be
dropped there too — but I don't have hardware to verify.

Tested on Pixel Fold (felix, gs201).

Cc: Peter Griffin <peter.griffin@linaro.org>
Cc: Alim Akhtar <alim.akhtar@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: Christopher L. Crutchfield <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
---
 drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c | 11 ++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c b/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
--- a/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
+++ b/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
@@ -2370,8 +2370,17 @@ static const struct exynos_ufs_drv_data gs101_ufs_drvs = {

 static const struct exynos_ufs_drv_data gs201_ufs_drvs = {
 	.uic_attr		= &gs101_uic_attr,
-	.quirks			= UFSHCD_QUIRK_PRDT_BYTE_GRAN |
-				  UFSHCI_QUIRK_SKIP_RESET_INTR_AGGR |
+	/*
+	 * gs101 sets UFSHCD_QUIRK_PRDT_BYTE_GRAN — gs201 must NOT.
+	 * gs201 controller follows UFS spec: the UTRD response_upiu_offset
+	 * and prd_table_offset fields are in DWORDS. With the quirk set,
+	 * mainline writes those fields in BYTES; the controller interprets
+	 * as DWORDS and writes the response 4× further into the UCD than
+	 * mainline reads back from. Result: link startup OK, NOP_OUT
+	 * "completes" with no UIC errors, but RSP UPIU appears empty
+	 * (controller actually wrote it at UCD+0x800 instead of UCD+0x200).
+	 */
+	.quirks			= UFSHCI_QUIRK_SKIP_RESET_INTR_AGGR |
 				  UFSHCI_QUIRK_BROKEN_REQ_LIST_CLR |
 				  UFSHCD_QUIRK_BROKEN_OCS_FATAL_ERROR |
 				  UFSHCI_QUIRK_SKIP_MANUAL_WB_FLUSH_CTRL |
--
